And now a page from the almanac of our Sunday Morning: September 30, 1882, exactly 136 years ago today, for those who can count correctly, the day the future physicist Johannes Wilhelm Hans Geiger was born in Germany.
Geiger developed a method to detect and measure radioactivity, an invention that eventually led to the device called the Geiger counter.
