A tsunami also struck western Donggala in 1996, killing nine.
Indonesia is located on the Pacific Ring of Fire and is often hit by earthquakes.
Here is a list of some of the most powerful earthquakes and tsunamis in recent years:
2004: A major earthquake on the west coast of the Indonesian province of Aceh in northern Sumatra on December 26 caused a tsunami that hit 14 countries and claimed a total of 226,000 lives along the Indian Ocean coast, more than half of them in Aceh.
2005: A series of severe earthquakes occurred on the west coast of Sumatra in late March and early April.
