2010: A 7.5-magnitude earthquake struck one of the Mentawai Islands, off the coast of Sumatra, and caused a 10-meter-high tsunami that destroyed dozens of villages and killed about 300 people.
2016: A shallow earthquake hit Pidie Regency in Aceh, causing destruction and panic as people were reminded of the devastation of the deadly 2004 earthquake and tsunami.
